It's kinda like Ethan
Frome finding his love

01:21:36.680 --> 01:21:40.433
in a visitor he never wanted
and then ruining her life.

01:21:43.320 --> 01:21:44.499
I am

01:21:44.500 --> 01:21:45.500
so

01:21:46.200 --> 01:21:48.223
So sorry, you guys.

01:21:49.480 --> 01:21:50.480
Fuck that.

01:21:53.060 --> 01:21:54.060
Ed's right.

01:21:55.510 --> 01:21:57.163
If their plan was to unite us,

01:21:58.280 --> 01:22:00.803
let's show them that their
plan worked a little too well.

01:22:02.350 --> 01:22:04.493
I'm tired of being told I'm a freak.

01:22:05.686 --> 01:22:08.423
It's time we stand up
for our way of lives.

01:22:11.670 --> 01:22:14.473
It's time we stand up
for our right to be alone.

01:22:15.380 --> 01:22:16.992
Together.

01:22:19.030 --> 01:22:20.863
Loners on three.

01:22:20.864 --> 01:22:21.930
One, two.

01:22:21.931 --> 01:22:22.989
Loners.

01:22:22.990 --> 01:22:24.073
Sorry, was I early?

01:22:29.130 --> 01:22:32.459
Call your boss, whoever that is,

01:22:32.460 --> 01:22:34.279
and tell him to get in here.

01:22:34.280 --> 01:22:35.333
We needa talk.

01:22:36.452 --> 01:22:38.869
You know, like, when you're able.

01:22:38.870 --> 01:22:40.869
Ha, hear that, Delgado?

01:22:40.870 --> 01:22:43.381
Get it done.

01:22:54.091 --> 01:22:55.409
What are your demands?

01:22:55.410 --> 01:22:59.329
Demands makes it sound like
it's a hostage situation.

01:22:59.330 --> 01:23:00.399
It's not.

01:23:00.400 --> 01:23:03.659
Okay, well what do
you want for Christmas?

01:23:03.660 --> 01:23:06.516
Set up Jeremy, or
whatever his real name is,

01:23:06.517 --> 01:23:08.579
and say we're the ones who stopped him.

01:23:08.580 --> 01:23:10.859
That's ridiculous, we
can't take the chance

01:23:10.860 --> 01:23:12.699
that any one of you will
blow the whole thing

01:23:12.700 --> 01:23:15.899
someday for some six-figure book deal.

01:23:15.900 --> 01:23:17.739
Looks like you're gonna have to.

01:23:17.740 --> 01:23:19.689
What's the alternative, killing all of us?

01:23:19.690 --> 01:23:21.289
There's a lotta cameras
out there, Delgado,

01:23:21.290 --> 01:23:23.609
that need an end to this
story, a bloodbath is not

01:23:23.610 --> 01:23:25.859
gonna look good for the program.

01:23:25.860 --> 01:23:28.089
What do you all want in return?

01:23:28.090 --> 01:23:32.359
To be taken off the watch
list, for one, permanently.

01:23:32.360 --> 01:23:33.526
That's all we ever wanted.

01:23:33.527 --> 01:23:35.621
And you have to let Clara go.

01:23:35.622 --> 01:23:37.839
You'll have to talk to
someone else about that.

01:23:37.840 --> 01:23:41.309
On her way to our facility,
our agents were ambushed

01:23:41.310 --> 01:23:43.873
and she was liberated.

01:23:45.160 --> 01:23:48.381
I'm guessing that was the work
of your friends, Mr. Chalk.

01:23:48.382 --> 01:23:49.499
Oh.

01:23:49.500 --> 01:23:51.229
Don't suppose you can
tell me anything about

01:23:51.230 --> 01:23:53.179
the secret organization that's destroying

01:23:53.180 --> 01:23:55.819
my career, is there?

01:23:55.820 --> 01:23:58.429
I had a hood over my
head the whole time.

01:23:58.430 --> 01:24:00.209
I never saw a thing.

01:24:00.210 --> 01:24:01.589
You expect me to believe that?

01:24:01.590 --> 01:24:04.140
I expect that it doesn't
matter what you believe.

01:24:05.130 --> 01:24:06.749
You think you can play the bad guy

01:24:06.750 --> 01:24:08.653
for a little while longer?

01:24:13.330 --> 01:24:14.330
Fine.

01:24:17.370 --> 01:24:18.540
But if any of this

01:24:19.530 --> 01:24:20.883
ever leaves this room,

01:24:22.120 --> 01:24:23.859
you all suffer,

01:24:23.860 --> 01:24:25.410
not just the one who leaked it.

01:24:26.620 --> 01:24:27.620
That understood?

01:24:29.240 --> 01:24:30.769
My most embarrassing failure

01:24:30.770 --> 01:24:34.169
was not seeing earlier the
imbecile you truly are.

01:24:34.170 --> 01:24:37.629
Come on, you're not
gonna be a part of this.

01:24:37.630 --> 01:24:39.283
Part of what?

01:24:40.970 --> 01:24:41.970
Exactly.

01:25:08.781 --> 01:25:13.781
Yeah, baby, yeah!

01:25:16.141 --> 01:25:17.229
You know, you play this right,

01:25:17.230 --> 01:25:19.270
I bet you get some acting jobs outta this.

01:25:19.271 --> 01:25:20.809
Oh, we can all get something outta this,

01:25:20.810 --> 01:25:22.300
whatever we want.

01:25:22.301 --> 01:25:23.889
I feel like I'm losing what I want.

01:25:23.890 --> 01:25:25.699
What do you mean, Dabney?

01:25:25.700 --> 01:25:27.779
It wasn't until I was
officially called a loner

01:25:27.780 --> 01:25:30.224
I finally had friends.

01:25:30.225 --> 01:25:32.379
Now you're, you're all leaving.

01:25:32.380 --> 01:25:35.619
You know, we never
actually did play poker.

01:25:35.620 --> 01:25:38.620
You'll never get tired of
taking people's money, will you?

01:25:39.713 --> 01:25:42.709
I do think it's probably a good idea

01:25:42.710 --> 01:25:44.629
that we all stay in touch.

01:25:44.630 --> 01:25:46.469
Can't believe I'm gonna
say this, but I propose

01:25:46.470 --> 01:25:49.299
that we get together
every once in a while.

01:25:49.300 --> 01:25:51.289
We could call it a support group.

01:25:51.290 --> 01:25:53.369
Say, once a week?

01:25:53.370 --> 01:25:54.773
We can meet at my place.

01:25:55.990 --> 01:25:57.033
Sound good, Dabney?

01:25:58.840 --> 01:25:59.840
Sounds good.

01:26:02.640 --> 01:26:03.640
Whoo.

01:26:04.860 --> 01:26:07.653
Well, get ready to
smile for the cameras.

01:26:10.400 --> 01:26:11.400
Let's go, guys.

01:26:15.410 --> 01:26:18.253
Hey, you know the one thing I don't get?

01:26:20.710 --> 01:26:23.293
How did Jeremy get tased?

01:26:26.503 --> 01:26:29.039
Musta been one of the Hughes
people, but I don't know how.

01:26:29.040 --> 01:26:31.139
You can't exactly get your
hands on those tasers,

01:26:31.140 --> 01:26:33.523
and you have to be at close range.

01:26:44.550 --> 01:26:45.793
Holy shit.

01:26:49.740 --> 01:26:51.869
Give Paige a high
position in whatever branch

01:26:51.870 --> 01:26:54.509
she wants, and check on
Clara from time to time

01:26:54.510 --> 01:26:56.023
to make sure she's doing well.

01:26:57.750 --> 01:27:00.740
We didn't fully succeed
in ending the war, but

01:27:01.690 --> 01:27:03.123
I feel like we did some good.

01:27:05.010 --> 01:27:06.010
No.

01:27:07.215 --> 01:27:08.665
I feel like we can trust him.

01:27:09.760 --> 01:27:11.860
In his heart, he believes in our struggle.

01:27:12.820 --> 01:27:15.573
Headband or not, Lincoln
Chalk is a true loner.

01:27:16.530 --> 01:27:17.530
They all are.

01:27:18.290 --> 01:27:19.400
God bless them.

01:27:20.297 --> 01:27:21.673
The best people on Earth.

01:27:23.437 --> 01:27:24.975
Good night, Tessman.
